    <text>
        <body>
            
            <div1 type="letter">
                
                <pb facs="nei.j4a.36.16"/>
                
                <fw type="curatorial">16</fw>
                
                <figure>
                    <figDesc>A Border of Daisies</figDesc>
                </figure>
                
                <note>
                    ans. 5/25/72
                    Dictated 
                </note>
                
                <opener>
                    <dateline>4 Feb., 1972</dateline>
                
                    <salute>Dear Dr. Neihardt&#8212;</salute>
                </opener>
                <p>I am at a very exciting period in my life, and I would like to give part of the credit to you.</p> 
                
                <p>When you were on the Dick Cavett Show, I sat spellbound through the entire program. I felt as though you were speaking directly to me, bringing me back to the basic truths I had strayed from for so long. (How much wiser was the "ignorant" red man who never lost sight of his ancestral guiding spirits than the white man who had <unclear>financed</unclear>, institutionalized, analyzed and categorized his religion until Truth was obscured.)</p> 
                
                <p>The message that came through from you to me was: "Go back to the basics. Be still, be simple; be spiritual. Commune with the 
                
                <pb facs="nei.j4a.36.17"/>
                    
                <fw type="curatorial">17</fw>
                <fw type="authorial">-2-</fw>
                    
                    voices within you, trust them, obey them. Worship your Creator, respect all His creations.</p> 
                
                <p>I am trying to follow this wisdom in the spirit of faith and simplicity that is so evident when you speak; and proportinately to how I succeed, I am finding new happiness, new courage, new serenity, new pride in living.</p> 
                
                <p>And so, thank you. Thank you very much.</p> 
                <closer>
                    <salute>Sincerely,</salute>
                
                    <signed>Cynthia Trenshaw</signed>
                </closer>
                
                <postscript>
                    <opener><hi rend="caps">P.S.</hi></opener> <p>I'd like very much to have you autograph my copy of <hi rend="underline">Black Elk Speaks</hi>. But, to save you the bother of repackaging and shipping the book back to me, would you please just autograph a piece of paper that I can affix inside the front of my book? I'd be most grateful. Again, thanks.</p> 
                        
                        <p>
                            <address>
                                <addrLine><hi rend="caps">MRS. CYNTHIA TRENSHAW</hi></addrLine>
                                <addrLine>4036 <hi rend="caps">VAN BUREN ST.</hi></addrLine> 
                                <addrLine><hi rend="caps">GARY, INDIANA</hi></addrLine> 
                                <addrLine>46408</addrLine>
                            </address>
                        </p>
                </postscript>
                
            </div1>
